Name: Mohd Zuhairi bin Mohd Zubir
Completion:
Here's the one thing I like about the SWITCH site:
- Integration of 'gamification' which allows staff to learn and keep track of their progress in a gaming-like environment, in line with the trends of the digital age and current generation

Here's the one thing I wish about the SWITCH Station:
- PETRONAS' digital strategy in Blockchain technology. 

While I applaud the organization's efforts in tapping the current and future trends in the digital age i.e. Big Data, AI, IoT, it seems that I couldn't find any info on our positioning on the Blockchain technology. Some experts predicted that Blockchain will disrupt our life just like what the Internet did in the 90s. 

While there are still kinks to work through, it is sure to impact nearly every industry in some form or another. While the implications of these “distributed ledgers” are still being realized, one thing is certain - early adopters will undoubtedly come out ahead of the curve - and I think PETRONAS can be that early adopters. Big energy companies such as Chevron and Statoil have already show their positioning in the game. Therefore, I'm curious to see what PETRONAS has in stores for this new technology that is going to change our lives.

Name: Abdul Jamal bin Khamis
Completion:
Data science. Data scientists bring meaning to large quantities of data by working in cross-functional teams to uncover patterns, gain insight, solve business pain points and drive value.

To make sense of the large amount of data, data scientists create analytic models using many tools such as R and Python. These are both well-known programming languages used in data science.

Besides creating algorithms, writing codes or visualising data, being a data scientist is also about having the right inquisitive mindset and soft skills.

With the right mindset, data scientists will always be open to new ideas and opportunities, and constantly be looking for ways to improve what they do. A good data scientist is also master of storytelling, a critical soft skill that allows data scientists to present meaningful and insightful results to their target audience.

Name: Zamaluddin Ali
Completion: creative and artistic. please look and prepare beyond conventional digital data application.You might have read or heard some science fiction text that describes how DNA can be used for data storage. As strange as it may sound, it actually has basis in real science. DNA has two desirable traits that no current data storage technology possesses. One, it can last for at most 2,000 years, sometimes even longer, without degrading. No CD, DVD, HDD, or SSD can claim to even be a hundred years old and still functional. Second, it has the a very high storage capacity. One cubic millimeter of DNA can store one exabyte of data, equivalent to one billion gigabytes.

Name: Ahmed Abdullah Abbas Al-Shuwili
Completion:
Between a traditional economy and a knowledge-based economy is a big difference. The former depends on traditional factors of production (that is, they depend on human labor and machines in a narrow range in all agricultural, industrial and service sectors), and there is no skilled and skilled labor, And its products are not competitive in the world and have a delayed infrastructure and lack of innovation and creativity.

Unlike the knowledge-based economy that uses high-skill skills based on knowledge, 70% of employment in advanced economies is information labor. Most factory workers are using their brains and minds more than their hands. Computer and Internet networks are widespread and contain medium-, high-tech and high-tech industries such as business services And financial services

Name: Abdullah bin Zainal Abidin
Completion:
I really like the mobile app layout and interface. Easy to navigate and the UX is surreal. Content wise, I particularly enjoy the outside-in chapters, as well as those things closer to home; Alpha Wells.

One wish I have is an explanation on how the pointing system works. I've written a feedback regarding the issue and have yet to receive a reply. It sounds rather petty but I still can't get my head around how some users are already level 14, and I've completed all my videos and challenges (I only got 1 or 2 wrong) but I'm only at level 13 max.

Name: Tina binti Zainudin
Completion:
Hello @Abdullah bin Zainal Abidin, thank you for your feedback and query. We understand your concern regarding the points and leveling, and hope that we can address it here. In the first few months of SWITCH, there were several SWITCH challenges that allowed users to gain extra/bonus points, e.g. referral challenges and bonanza week challenges. Thus, those who were early adopters had an early boost in their levels and points. 
Do look out for these challenges to earn more points. Thank you for your support and we hope you will continue to enjoy SWITCH!
